<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-foreigntext" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Foreign</head>
    <p>The <gi>foreign</gi> element identifies a word or phrase as belonging to a language other than that of the surrounding text. <!-- Explain that language codes can be added --></p>
    <p><specList>
        <specDesc key="foreign"/>
    </specList>
    </p> 
    
    <p></p>
    
    <cit>
        <quote><!-- conventional rendering --></quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>...</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="panciera">
        <foreign xml:lang="la">lapis philosophicus</foreign>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london" corresp="http://inslib.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT021.html">
        For the lost line 6 Aurigemma, loc. cit., suggests <foreign xml:lang="la">matris castrorum</foreign>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="ddbdp" corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;4;1094"> 
        <foreign xml:lang="cop"> <num value="3">γ</num> lin</foreign>
    </egXML>
    
    <div xml:id="trans-foreigntext-responsibility">
        
        <!-- ddbdp example is from milestone 4, line 1  -->
    
        <head>Responsibility for this section</head>
        <listBibl>
            <bibl><respStmt><resp>author</resp><name>Charlotte Tupman</name></respStmt></bibl>
            <bibl><respStmt><resp>author</resp><name>Gabriel Bodard</name></respStmt></bibl>
        </listBibl>
    </div>
</div>
